snippet: Caroline Ouellette scored in overtime, lifting Canada to a win over the United States in the gold medal game of the Women’s World Championship in Burlington, Vt.
abstract: Canadian women's hockey team defeats United States, 5-4, in the gold medal game of the Women’s World Championship.
lead_paragraph: Caroline Ouellette scored in overtime, lifting Canada to a win over the United States in the gold medal game of the Women’s World Championship in Burlington, Vt.
